            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Vidya Vikas Mandal runs three schools there. Lower groups, Primary, secondary (marathi and English mediums). Marathi is Janata High School and Eng is St Francis.\nI personally studied in Janata High School till 10th in year 2006 pass out.\n\nToday my kid is taking education in 2nd std in st francis.\nAs far I feel that St Francis School is not upto the mark in trachings as I can not see progress in my kids education.\n\nWithout going School his handwriting, poem learning or memorizing was awesome in lockdown. Bt not I can't see School is focusing on many aspects of education.\n\nNo parent meetings held till date.\n\nNo updates or feedback from teachers on time.\n\nIt was my problem that I hv decided to take admission in this school.\n\nNot only me, other parents hv same issues which I hv discussed with them personally.\n\nOther facilities are also poor.\n\nIn brief I wud like to recommend this School if r u not getting admission in other schools at 11th hr.\n\nOther wise u can skip this school.\n\nThanks",
